Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Combine walnuts and SPLENDA(R) Brown Sugar Blend in small bowl. Place 3/4 cup of walnut mixture in pie shell. Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, SPLENDA(R) Sugar Blend, eggs, pumpkin pie spice and salt in medium bowl; mix well. Pour batter over nuts. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F; bake 40 to 50 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Combine butter and remaining walnut mixture; stir until moistened. Sprinkle over cooled pie. Broil about 5 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly. Cool before serving.